China Small Firms’ Biggest Problem Is Rising Costs, Adviser Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-10-20T08:58:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/china-small-firms-biggest-problem-is-rising-costs-adviser-says.html
The biggest problem facing small and
medium-sized companies in  China  is rising costs rather than
financing, Zhou Qiren, an adviser to the People’s Bank of China,
said in  Shanghai .  The government should reduce taxes for smaller businesses,
Zhou said at a conference in the city.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nerys Avery at 
 navery2@bloomberg.net  